      "askDjNotificationsText": "Apple clients can use optional push notifications as wake or attention hints for Ask DJ sync. Push contains no tokens, full replies, audio or history; the app fetches content through Home Assistant.",
      "askDjPrivacyTitle": "Privacy kept compact",
      "askDjPrivacyText": "Clients do not store your persistent Music DNA profile. Spotify credentials stay in Home Assistant. Music DNA must not store OAuth tokens, bearer tokens, raw audio, full prompts or unbounded Spotify listening history.",
      "askDjPiTitle": "Raspberry Pi follows along",
      "askDjPiText": "On Raspberry Pi, Ask DJ uses readonly_actions: history/status display plus Home Assistant-provided structured action buttons. No Pi voice, free text, TTS or local audio; ESP uses the PTT/playback command flow without Ask DJ chat history.",
      "askDjRequirementsTitle": "What you need",
      "askDjRequirementsText": "Home Assistant, HACS DJConnect integration v3.2.5 or newer, a music backend, local pairing and, for voice/audio, an Assist pipeline with STT/TTS. Spotify Premium and Client ID are only needed for Spotify Direct; Music Assistant uses its own providers.",
      "aiPrivacyTitle": "AI privacy-first",
      "aiPrivacyText": "DJConnect is designed as a Home Assistant-first system. The Home Assistant integration orchestrates Ask DJ, playback, Assist/STT/TTS and Music DNA; DJConnect's active integration routes use Home Assistant Assist/STT/TTS and do not call direct external AI/STT/TTS APIs.",
      "clientTransparencyTitle": "Transparent clients",
      "clientTransparencyText": "The Music DNA dashboard fetches cards such as Summary, Favorite genres, Favorite artists, Energy profile, Mood/taste direction, Recent tracks, Based on and Updated from Home Assistant; clients do not reconstruct a local source profile.",
      "faqAskDjDnaQuestion": "Does Ask DJ require Music DNA?",
      "faqAskDjDnaAnswer": "No. Ask DJ works without Music DNA. Without opt-in, Ask DJ does not use stored personal Music DNA context.",
      "faqDnaStoredQuestion": "Where is Music DNA stored?",
      "faqDnaStoredAnswer": "Music DNA is server-side in Home Assistant. Clients do not store your persistent Music DNA profile.",
      "faqDnaDeleteQuestion": "Can I delete Music DNA?",
      "faqDnaDeleteAnswer": "You can clear Music DNA at any time. If Music DNA remains enabled, DJConnect starts learning again from an empty profile.",
      "faqSpotifyQuestion": "Does DJConnect store Spotify credentials on devices?",
      "faqSpotifyAnswer": "No. Spotify credentials stay in Home Assistant. ESP32 stores no Spotify credentials and receives no Ask DJ chat history.",
      "faqCloudQuestion": "Does DJConnect send raw audio or prompts to its own cloud?",
      "faqCloudAnswer": "No. Raw audio is not stored by default and diagnostics contain no raw audio, full prompts, Ask DJ history or Music DNA dumps.",
      "faqSpotifyAffiliationQuestion": "Is DJConnect affiliated with Spotify?",
      "faqSpotifyAffiliationAnswer": "DJConnect is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by Spotify AB.",
